<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>NagVis on Tech Notebook</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/tags/nagvis/</link><description>Recent content in NagVis on Tech Notebook</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 28 Apr 2025 18:51:06 +0200</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://wiki.deimos.fr/tags/nagvis/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>NagVis: Map Your Architecture with Nagios Alerts</title><link>https://wiki.deimos.fr/NagVis:_Cartographier_son_architecture_avec_ses_alertes_nagios/</link><pubDate>Tue, 11 Mar 2008 07:33:00 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://wiki.deimos.fr/NagVis:_Cartographier_son_architecture_avec_ses_alertes_nagios/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>NagVis is a really great product, easy to use but not to install. That&amp;rsquo;s why I did this documentation. You also need to install NDOUtils. We&amp;rsquo;ll see the installation too.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="ndoutils">NDOUtils &lt;a href="#ndoutils" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;h3 id="prepair-system">Prepair System &lt;a href="#prepair-system" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h3>&lt;p>Make sure your System meets the requirements:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Nagios v2.X (stable) is running&lt;/li>
&lt;li>mysql (Version &amp;gt; 4)&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
